The paper proposes a class of robust stochastic subgradient methods for distributed learning from heterogeneous datasets in the presence of Byzantine workers. The paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it deals with learning from data. It may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it deals with distributed learning. Additionally, the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it proposes a method to mitigate the negative effects of Byzantine attacks. The paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category as it deals with controlling the effects of Byzantine attacks. Finally, the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category as it deals with the transmission of information in the presence of Byzantine attacks.
